* =============================================================================
* tb_pcn_route_test.spice — 16×32 module + routing layer_link integration test
* Simulator: ngspice 42+
* Run via:   ./run_sim.sh --netlist tb_pcn_route_test.spice
*
* Circuit: pcn_module_16x32 (mod0) + layer_link_route_16 (routing link)
*   - mod0 row 0: inp_col_0=1.0V (+200mV above vcm=0.8V) → active differential input
*   - All other columns balanced at vcm=0.8V
*   - All 512 MAC weights initialised to 0.75V via .ic
*   - Routing weight[0][0] pre-initialized to 0.75V to demonstrate Hebbian LTD write
*     (all other routing weights at ~0V via 10GΩ bleeders)
*   - vbias_n=0.760V for SF tail transistors in layer_link
*   - vcm_route=0.65V routing Hebbian reference
*   - PMOS SF (§71): sf_out ≈ iout_balance + |Vgs_P| ≈ 0.47 + 0.67 = 1.14V (LTP possible)
*
* Single tran (400ns), WE_route period=50ns (fires at t=50,100,150,200,250,300,350ns):
*   t=0–50ns:   Settle — vw_route[0][0]=0.75V → XMPRED_r sinks ~28µA → ierr_dig=HIGH
*   t=50–55ns:  WE_route pulse 1 — Hebbian fires: sf_out≈1.14V (PMOS SF; §71)
*   t=100–105n: WE_route pulse 2 — LTD continues (weight decreasing)
*   t=380ns:    T2 observations — trained state after 7 LTD pulses
* =============================================================================
.title PCN 16x32 routing test

.lib "$PDK_ROOT/sky130A/libs.tech/ngspice/sky130.lib.spice" tt
.include "pcn_mac_cell.spice"
.include "pcn_array_16x32.spice"
.include "pcn_module_16x32.spice"
.include "layer_link_route_16.spice"

.options RELTOL=1e-3 ABSTOL=1e-12 GMIN=1e-12

* ── Supply rails ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Vdd   vdd  0  DC 1.8
Vss   vss  0  DC 0
Vcm   vcm  0  DC 0.8
Vpi   vpi  0  DC 0.65
Vcm_route  vcm_route  0  DC 0.65
Vcm_iout  ncm_iout  0  DC 0.47
Vbias_n  vbias_n  0  DC 0.760
Vbias_p  vbias_p  0  DC 0.88

* ── Column inputs — mod0 (16 rows × 32 cols) ─────────────────────────────────
* Row 0 active: inp_col_0=1.0V, inn_col_0=vcm=0.8V (+200mV differential)
* All other columns: balanced at vcm
Vinp0  m0_inp0  0  DC 1.0
Vinn0  m0_inn0  0  DC 0.8
Vinp1  m0_inp1  0  DC 0.8
Vinn1  m0_inn1  0  DC 0.8
Vinp2  m0_inp2  0  DC 0.8
Vinn2  m0_inn2  0  DC 0.8
